    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hey there Algolia Team, I've been following this issue because i've come across a similar need in my app. I'm using the react-instantsearch library and I'm in love with it, but this is one of the pieces I found missing. Although my application is slightly different, it's the same feature set that @jaarkko ended up implementing at [meetingpackage.com/search](meetingpackage.com/search). \r\n\r\n1. The ability to filter results by a location input (with location autocomplete)\r\n2. The ability to filter results by a map bounding box (eg. \"Search within map\")\r\n\r\nUsing your [Tourism demo](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/react/examples/tourism/) as an example, a user would have a hard time finding a place to stay if they couldn't filter by location.\r\n\r\nI've included a mockup of how we're planning on implement it. For the time being, i've just removed the geo search feature hoping you guys would build a react widget for it. 🙂\r\n\r\nDo you think this is something that would fit into the scope of the react-instantsearch library?\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1194\" alt=\"screen shot 2017-01-18 at 8 29 08 am\" src=\"https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/5359194/22072925/c35776a0-dd58-11e6-8a4b-35b224a1443c.png\">\r\n",
